        <h2 class="science-person-center__title text-size-biggest text-theme-color text-weight-bold">Person Centered Care</h2>
        <div>
          <p class="text-size-big text-line-height text-weight-light">Person-centred care (PCC) is a holistic and integrative approach designed to maintain well-being and quality of life for people with dementia, and it includes the elements of care, the individual, the carers, and the family. Following its introduction in the 1990s, clinical studies have shown that PCC interventions can reduce challenging behaviours and improve the quality of life, and PCC  is now established best practice for dementia care throughout the world. However, the effectiveness of interventions for PCC critically depends of the unique characteristics of not only the person with dementia, but also on the carers providing the intervention. Thus, maintaining the good function of the dementia care triad is crucial to enabling sustainable and effective person centred care in practical settings</p>
        </div>
