            <p class="text-size-big text-weight-light text-line-height">also known as behavioural and psychological symptoms of dementia (BPSD) is a collective term used to describe behaviours such as agitation, insomnia, restlessness, hallucinations, anxiety and depressed mood. CB can cause significant distress to people with dementia, their families and caregivers, and often lead to premature institutionalization, increased care burden and medical cost. Currently there are no effective drug treatments for CB, and psychosocial interventions are recommended as first line treatment in most situations</p>
